The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the Vice President's Residence on Memorial Day, thanking veterans for their service and honoring those who did not come home. He expressed his gratitude to Project Hero and its organizers for their efforts in supporting veterans and creating a sense of community through cycling. Pence also praised Secretary of Veterans Affairs, David Shulkin, for his work in improving healthcare for veterans. He mentioned that President Donald Trump has signed executive orders and legislation to ensure effective and accountable care for veterans. Pence concluded by wishing the veterans a safe journey and a full recovery, emphasizing that the American people are grateful for their service.